Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces (if carrots are on the larger side, halve lengthwise first).

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{drizzle}, @salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While carrots roast, trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Drain and rinse @Lentils{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{drizzle} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add lentils, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{4%tablespoon}, @Chili Powder{1%teaspoon}, and @water{2%tablespoon}; stir until combined. Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> TIP: If lentils seem too soupy, increase the heat under the pot and cook until thickened to your liking.

Stir @Crème Fraîche{2%tablespoon} and @Butter{1%TBSP} into pot with lentils. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. (If chicken begins to brown too quickly, lower heat.) Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken for pork. Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Heat pan used for chicken over medium heat; add @water{1/4%cup}, @Red Pepper Jam{1}, and @Butter{1%TBSP}. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted and sauce has thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise. Divide chicken, creamed lentils, and carrots between plates in separate sections. Spoon pepper jam sauce over chicken; sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve.

> Thinly slice pork crosswise.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.